  "description": "Gravemark Asteroid constitutes a cold, irregular minor body set along one of Saltharrow System’s charted debris lanes, its orbit fixed by the system’s pronounced gravitic gradients. The surface presents dark, vitrified regolith and exposed nickel-iron ribs, cut by ancient impact hollows that cast permanent shadow. A weak, intermittent dust halo follows its rotation, briefly flaring when the hard white radiance of the primary star strikes freshly fractured faces. Its stable ephemerides serve as a consistent positional reference within the compact system’s navigational canon.",
